The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically named entity recognition (NER), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes new models to improve the performance of NER, which is a task related to optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses datasets related to text classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
